<subSubSection id="C30198A6FFF2FFCAFF02FEE4FCEF77F8" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA4CB2DFFF2FFCAFF02FEE4FF2574F8" blockId="14.[130,775,376,657]" box="[132,207,376,402]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">NOTES</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA4CB2DFFF2FFCAFF02FE04FCEF77F8" blockId="14.[130,775,376,657]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AB6DCFFF2FFCAFF02FE04FE9B74D9" author="LECOMTE H." box="[132,369,407,434]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" pagination="99 - 121" refId="ref13173" refString="LECOMTE H. 1928 a. - Ebenacees nouvelles de l'Indochine. Notulae Systematicae 4 (4): 99 - 121. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 6463259" type="journal article" year="1928">Lecomte (1928a: 118)</bibRefCitation>
cited 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF2FFCAFE29FE04FDC374D9" box="[431,553,407,433]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Pierre 5026</emphasis>
from “Cochinchine: Bao chiang, province de Bien hoa” as the original material. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AB6DCFFF2FFCAFF00FE4BFEBE7499" author="NGUYEN T. H." box="[134,340,471,497]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127" pagination="63 - 74" refId="ref13500" refString="NGUYEN T. H. 1996. - Fam. Ebenaceae Gurke, in AVERYANOV L. V., NGUYEN T. B., NGUYEN T. H., PHAN K. L., SEROV V. P. &amp; AKIMOVA G. A. (eds), Vascular Plants Synopsis of Vietnamese Flora. Russian Academy of Sciences, Saint Petersburg, Russia and National Center for Natural Sciences and Technology of Vietnam: 63 - 74." type="book chapter" year="1996">Nguyen (1996: 71)</bibRefCitation>
cited 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF2FFCAFE12FE44FDE57499" box="[404,527,471,497]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Pierre 5026</emphasis>
(P) as the 
<typeStatus id="54A0758FFFF2FFCAFD06FE4BFD087499" box="[640,738,471,497]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">holotype</typeStatus>
. As this collection does not comprise a single sheet, a second-step lectotypification needs to be made. Four sheets of 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF2FFCAFD0AFD8BFCEF7758" box="[652,773,534,560]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">Pierre 5026</emphasis>
have been located at P and VNM and have Lecomte’s determination and a detailed label. Here, we designate P00721703, the best preserved specimen from the P collection as the 
<typeStatus id="54A0758FFFF2FFCAFD18FDEAFCEB77F8" box="[670,769,630,656]" pageId="14" pageNumber="127">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
